dcterms:description: A dataset collected and de-identified by a US-based tele-dermatology service, containing images of skin conditions taken using consumer-grade digital cameras. The dataset includes cases from 12,306 unique patients with significant variations in pose, lighting, and body parts.
dcterms:title: Dermatology Dataset

dcterms:description: A large open-source dataset of de-identified chest radiograph images, consisting of 224,316 chest radiographs from 65,240 unique patients. The dataset includes labels for 14 radiological observations extracted from radiology reports.
dcterms:title: CheXpert Dataset

dcterms:description: A hospital-scale chest X-ray database containing 112,120 de-identified X-rays from 30,805 unique patients, used for weakly-supervised classification and localization of common thorax diseases.
dcterms:title: NIH Chest X-ray Dataset

dcterms:description: A large dataset used for contrastive learning of visual representations, consisting of 14 million images and 21.8K classes, commonly used for pretraining in various computer vision tasks.
dcterms:title: ImageNet Dataset
